Instance downgrade
***********************************

1. jenkins cron stop
2. stop the elastic search
3. stop the aws instance & select the instance type
4. cd /usr/share/elasticsearch/bin/ & vim elasticsearch.in.sh
5. Change the ES_MIN_MEM and ES_MAX_MEM value 24g to 10g or how much we want
6. cd /etc/sysconfig vim elasticsearch Change the heep size to 10gb or how much we assigned 
6. start the instance.
7. start the elastic search as well as cron in jenkins

 Volume downgrade/upgrade
 *********************************

 1. jenkins cron stop
 2. stop the services
 3. Create & attach the EBS volume
 4. fdisk -l  -- datapath name volume name                                                                         | /dev/xvdf
 5. mkfs.ext4 [volume path]                                                                                        | mkfs.ext4 /dev/xvdf
 6. mount [volume path] [directory name]                                                                           | mount /dev/xvdf /home/ubuntu/gokul/
 7. df -h 
 8. after that we need to give chown elasticsearch.elasticsearch [directory name]
 9. check blkid
 10./etc/fstab [add the blk id with dir]  i.e UUID=0000-000-000-0000980asd / esdata  ext4 errors-remount-ro 0 2
  
 mv  -v ~/Downloads/* ~/Videos/

 Modify Volume Add
 sudo growpart /dev/xvda1 [path]
 lsblk
 sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1 [path]
 df -h

  
